Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery vessel, the fabric is partially grey in section, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and remains of three lines of black-painted demotic (?) text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393901) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393901)
